{
  "$comment": [
    "Ground-truth labels for the detection benchmark. Each key is a corpus file",
    "path relative to packages/core/test/benchmark/corpus/. The value is the array",
    "of findings the scanner is EXPECTED to produce, each described by its stable",
    "ruleId plus (where applicable) the classical algorithm family and the hndl",
    "(harvest-now-decrypt-later) flag. Negative / false-positive bait files map to",
    "an empty array: any finding on them is a regression. The `category` is",
    "informational and drives the per-category breakdown in the scorer.",
    "These labels are hand-derived from packages/core/src/detectors/* and verified",
    "against the live detectors; see docs/validation/detection-benchmark.md."
  ],
  "positive/rsa-keygen-sign.ts": {
    "category": "rsa",
    "expected": [
      { "ruleId": "node-crypto-keygen", "algorithm": "RSA", "hndl": true },
      { "ruleId": "node-crypto-sign", "algorithm": "unknown", "hndl": false }
    ]
  },
